  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals are typically obligated to report suspicious transactions to designated authorities. The specific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n\n1. Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n2. Reporting large cash transactions\n3. Filing Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n4. Conducting due diligence on customers\n5. Maintaining transaction records\n\nThe exact details depend on the specific laws of each country.",
